From: Wener <wenermail@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] input: format time64 chunk names safely on x86

Alpine x86 uses a 64-bit time_t with a 32-bit long. Formatting tv_sec
with %lu causes a varargs type mismatch and can make tv_nsec read as zero,
colliding chunk filenames created in the same second.

Format tv_sec through an explicit int64_t cast and keep tv_nsec matched to
its long type.
---
 src/flb_input_chunk.c | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/src/flb_input_chunk.c
+++ b/src/flb_input_chunk.c
@@ -43,0 +44 @@
+#include <inttypes.h>
@@ -521 +522 @@
-             "%i-%lu.%4lu.flb",
+             "%i-%" PRId64 ".%4ld.flb",
@@ -523 +524 @@
-             tm.tm.tv_sec, tm.tm.tv_nsec);
+             (int64_t) tm.tm.tv_sec, tm.tm.tv_nsec);
